-- Barbie U.S. sales down 21 percent in second-quarter: CFO
-- 
-- Fri Jul 18, 2008 8:54am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/18/us-mattel-barbie-idUSN1826726420080718

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Sales of toymaker Mattel Inc's MAT.N iconic Barbie dolls were down 21 percent in the United States in the second quarter, its chief financial officer, Kevin Farr, said on Friday. 

 Farr's comments came after Mattel reported a quarterly profit that topped expectations, and also posted a 6-percent decrease in worldwide Barbie sales. (Reporting by  Aarthi Sivaraman , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)